'''Cross Creeks National Wildlife Refuge''' is a part of the U.S. system of [[National Wildlife Refuge]]s located along the [[Lake Barkley]] impoundment of the [[Cumberland River]] in [[Stewart County, Tennessee]] near [[Dover, Tennessee|Dover]], covering {{convert|8862|acre|km2}}.  It provides habitat for a wide variety of waterfowl and aquatic plant life in what is a largely [[wetlands]] environment.  Cross Creeks is the only National Wildlife Refuge located entirely in [[Middle Tennessee]] [[2006|as of 2006]].

